CYBERSECURITY THREAT
It is an action exploiting a vulnerability that results in harm to a network or computer system.
An attack vector is a method used by a bad actor to illegally access or inhibit a network,System,or facility

Three components that comprise an attack vector
1.Vulnerability
2.Malware
3.Pathway
=====================================
Main cybersecurity Threat Categories
1.SOCIAL ENGINEERING
2.MALWARE
3.UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS
4.SYSTEM DESIGN FAILURE

1.SPEAR PHISHING=>This type of phishing attack is focused on a specific individual or group of individuals,unlike a regular phishing attack,which is agnostic and doesn't distinguish between targets
2.DoS and DDoS=>A DDoS has infected many computers,which the bad actor controls by the way of the C&C server.
3.Ransomware=>It is a type of malware that denies the user access to a system or information,often through encryption.

===========================================
COMMON CYBERSECURITY ATTACK VECTORS
Birthday Attack=>The attack exploits a weakness that exists in some hashing algorithmss.
The weakness is that multiple input values produced the same output value.
Brute force=>A brute force attack is a hacking method that uses trial and error to crack passwords, login credentials, and encryption keys
